cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.NI, cs.CE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper studies the properties of the Google matrix of real networks, including the Wikipedia articles hyperlink network. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the Arnoldi method is used to analyze the distribution of eigenvalues in the complex plane. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper discusses the organization of information flow on web sites. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is another possible category as the paper deals with network communities and the hyperlink network of Wikipedia articles. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper uses mathematical methods to analyze the properties of the Google matrix.
